  <li><strong>Worried about joints and growth rate (every Golden owner should be)?</strong> <a href="#butternut-box-puppy">Butternut Box</a> and <a href="#years-puppy">Years</a> pre-portion to lean growth automatically — the easiest way to avoid the overfeeding that punishes a big-breed pup's hips and elbows.</li>
  <li><strong>Focused on coat, skin and long-term health?</strong> Fresh, whole-food recipes — <a href="#butternut-box-puppy">Butternut Box</a> and <a href="#years-puppy">Years</a> — carry the omega-3 and natural antioxidants a Golden's coat and high cancer risk make worth prioritising.</li>
  <li><strong>Want one food from puppy to senior?</strong> <a href="#forthglade-cold-pressed-puppy">Forthglade</a> is all-life-stage, so there's no awkward switch at 12–18 months.</li>
  <li><strong>After the highest nutrition?</strong> <a href="#years-puppy">Years</a> (95% AADF) and <a href="#butternut-box-puppy">Butternut Box</a> (93–94%) lead the field.</li>
  <li><strong>On a budget (and a Golden eats a lot)?</strong> <a href="#pooch-and-mutt-puppy">Pooch &amp; Mutt</a> is the value grain-free kibble pick.</li>
