<p>Across all of it, two rules matter most for a Golden: <strong>weigh every meal</strong> (and count treats in the daily total), and aim for steady, lean growth rather than a big, fast-growing puppy. Keep exercise age-appropriate too — avoid forced runs, long walks or repetitive jumping while the growth plates are still open, as that compounds joint risk. Keep an eye on skin, coat and ears given the breed's allergy tendency, and if appetite, weight, coat condition or toileting changes noticeably and doesn't settle, book a vet check.</p>

